ce:section.ce:para:
The humidity resistance of Mn4+-doped fluoride phosphors poses challenges for their practical applications. The phosphors prepared in this study were immersed in water to investigate their humidity resistance, following which the variation in their luminescence intensity was monitored. Results showed that the yellow color of the KSFMG-PE samples also remained unchanged after immersion for 480 min in water and that different extents of hydrolysis could be observed for KSFM, KSFMG-P, and KSFMG-E (Fig. 7
                        a). Fig. 7b reveals that the emission intensity of KSFMG-PE is 93.2 %, which is considerably higher than that of KSFM (55.0 %), KSFMG-P (83.7 %), and KSFMG-E (81.2 %) (detailed emission spectra are shown in Fig. 8
                        ). Compared with previous studies (Table S1), all the results indicate that KSFMG-PE has favorable IQE and humidity-resistance properties.

We next sought to interpret the anti-TQ phenomenon caused by GQDs. Accordingly, we obtained the temperature-dependent emission intensities of KSFM and KSFMG from the recorded emission spectra in the wavelength ranges of 580–620 nm (I

                           a
                        ) and 620–680 nm (I

                           s
                        ) (Fig. 10
                        a).
